@10032   = ~Friend of the Faithless~
@10033   = ~A ring is a small band of precious metal that is used as jewelry.  Some rare rings have had enchantments placed upon them that confer various magical abilities.  These rings are highly sought after, especially by those of the adventuring profession.~
@10034   = ~A man who scorns the gods is alone indeed, particularly when he himself needs divine favor in the form of healing. With that in mind, Tarvo the Unbeliever, a notorious Neverwinter thief, commissioned this ring from a patient and remarkably tolerant high priest of Tyr. Its enchantments enabled Tarvo to avoid the necessity of going to the temple when his professsion endangered his health. Unfortunately, no enchantment placed on the ring could have helped the luckless Tarvo, as no spell can reunite the body with its head, once a garotte has parted them. 


STATISTICS:

Wearer is Immune to Poison
Casts Heal once per Day
Dexterity Bonus:  1
Armor Class Bonus:  1
Saving Throw Bonus:  3~
@10035   = ~Amulet of Freedom~
@10036   = ~Amulets are usually magical devices that are commonly worn around the neck, suspended from a chain. The type of chain that comes with an amulet generally increases the item's aesthetic value, not its magical properties. Only one amulet can be dangled from the neck at a time.~
@10037   = ~Amulet of Freedom: 'Basil's Escape'

Basil Swiftbough's name will live on in his native Tethyr not because of the great deeds accomplished during his lifetime or because of the endowments he made to charitable institutions, but because the descendants of the 182 children he fathered are still trying to figure out where Basil hid the treasure that enabled him to live a life of ease, seducing village maidens and naive noblewomen alike in his quest for the perfect lover. One item that has been recovered from this alleged hoard is this Amulet of Freedom. While it may not have prevented the siring of any of his numerous progeny, it undoubtably contributed to his ability to evade potential entanglements once the lady's condition became known. In addition to a minor bonus to charisma, this amulet enables the wearer to ignore any hindrance that might afffect his mobility, and grants a small measure of protection in the form of a bonus to saving throws. Some people have all the luck.


STATISTICS:

Special:  The wearer is immune to everything,  magical and otherwise,  that affects mobility in any way.  This includes haste and slow spells.
Charisma Bonus:  1
Saving Throw Bonus:  1
Not Usable By:
